$interpreted: Slums Grandma: Drasted monsters! Come any closer and I'll...
Angelia: BE GONE!
Angelia: Ma'am, are you alright?
Slums Grandma: I'm fine, thanks to you, dear...
Angelia: Good. Now return home quickly and hide!
Lio: Angel!
Angelia: Lio! What are you doing here? Didn't Hyacinthus take you home?
Lio: He did, but then Cin went off to help the others. I heard they're overwhelmed at the outskirts,
Lio: but I can't find Nigel! What should I do?
Angelia: Over at the outskirts? Naya!
Naya: Roger that!
Lio: Wait, I'm coming too!
Hyacinthus: Told you both not to play here! Why won't you listen...
Slums Older Brother: ...Cin, I'm sorry...
Hyacinthus: Don't cry yet. Once I've brought you all home safely, we're gonna have a serious talk.
Hyacinthus: ...*breathes heavily*...
Hyacinthus: UrghhhAHHH!!
Angelia: Hyacinthus!
Lio: Cin, you ok?!
Hyacinthus: Lio? What are you doing here!? How many times do I have to tell you!?
Angelia: Don't blame Lio, he was worried sick...
Hyacinthus: Where are the children? Are the children hurt? Did I take care of everyone? Did I do well...?
Naya: They're fine. Not even a scratch on 'em!
Hyacinthus: ...Good...I've finally helped Nigel to protect everyone...finally helped him...
Angelia: It's not safe here. Let's bring Hyacinthus back to the big house. Naya, you take the children home.
Naya: Understood.
